    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Seems like the issue is actually not with the ETH1 WS connection, but actually with the prometheus `powchain.Service`. It is not able to detect that the connection was re-established and continues to report unhealthy state:\r\n```\r\ntime=\"2020-01-06 13:20:08\" level=debug msg=\"Latest eth1 chain event\" blockHash=0x0a64e5bb5fe4db5ac6e0cd60779df9017ef774bee6e632821ffcf1e99cddb170 blockNumber=28831 prefix=powchain\r\ntime=\"2020-01-06 13:20:08\" level=warning msg=\"Node is unhealthy!\" prefix=prometheus statuses=\"*rpc.Service: OK\r\n*prometheus.Service: OK\r\n*p2p.Service: OK\r\n*powchain.Service: ERROR websocket: close 1006 (abnormal closure): unexpected EOF\r\n*operations.Service: OK\r\n*blockchain.Service: OK\r\n*initialsync.Service: OK\r\n*sync.Service: OK\r\n```\r\nIf running in Kubernetes cluster, it will trigger unnecessary pod restart as the liveness probe will fail.",
